Jaw-dropping collection of extremely groovy Jazz and Soul tracks from the late '60s and early '70s, courtesy of the Atlantic and Warner Brothers labels. Although not as Psychedelic as their Rock counterparts, these exhilarating tracks are still very soul-expanding and mind-blowing! Features far out selections by Gary Burton ('Vibrafinger'), Freddie Hubbard ('This Is Combat I Know'), Charles Lloyd ('Sorcery'), Yusef Lateef ('Back Home'), Eddie Harris ('Smoke Signals') and more, including the very rare 'Spontaneous Simplicity' by the man who was born Psychedelic, Sun Ra. Warner.
